# =============================================================================
# Environment Variables Example (API)
# =============================================================================
# 
# This project uses EnvManager-MCP for secure, encrypted environment management
# See: .cursor/rules/security/secrets-management.mdc
#
# To set up environment variables:
# 1. Use MCP envx tool to initialize: `envx.init`
# 2. Set variables: `envx.set` with key-value pairs
#
# This file shows the expected variables but does NOT contain actual values.
# Actual values are stored encrypted in ~/.envvault/{projectId}/
# =============================================================================

# Database Connection
# PostgreSQL connection string
ConnectionStrings__DefaultConnection=Host=localhost;Database=robot_template;Username=postgres;Password=

# Logging
# Serilog minimum log level
Serilog__MinimumLevel__Default=Debug

# JWT Configuration (if using JWT auth)
# JWT signing key (generate via envx.rotateKeys)
# JWT__Secret=
# JWT__Issuer=https://yourapp.com
# JWT__Audience=https://yourapp.com
# JWT__ExpiryMinutes=30

# =============================================================================
# Notes:
# - Connection strings use ASP.NET Core configuration format (__ for nesting)
# - Never commit actual connection strings or secrets
# - Use envx tool for all secret management
# - For production, use Azure Key Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, or similar
# =============================================================================


